list.abstract: 深圳电子产品质量检测中心（以下简称SET）于1985年成立。是具有独立法人资格的公正检测机构，是电子、信息、通信、医疗产品测试技术公共服务平台。经过20多年的奋斗，已成功获得了“国家级计量认证合格单位”、“中国合格评定国家认可委员会（CNAS）认可实验室”、“国家强制性产品认证（3C）指定检测机构”、“国家节能产品认证指定检测机构”、“高新技术产品成果鉴定指定检测单位”、“深圳市电子产品质量监督检验机构”、“深圳口岸电子产品进出口商检单位”等20余项国内外重要资质。

yingyinNormal.en: Around the city of Zhaoqing, eight stations have been set up for the bikers to shake out there soaking ponchos and stop for food.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在肇庆市附近，路上有为骑行者设置的8个站点，能让他们脱下浸透了的雨披，停下来吃些东西。

yingyinNormal.en: A lot of toes were stepped on in order to set this up for today. And frankly, I really don't know what you gentlemen plan to gain by it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了设置好今天的这套演示设备，可是折腾了不少人，坦白说，我真不明白你们两位想达到什么目的。

yingyinNormal.en: Lab's all set up, boss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 实验室准备就绪了，老大。

yingyinNormal.en: Then one day, I saw you set down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 突然有一天，你出现了。

yingyinNormal.en: They had set a bulldozer on fire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 点燃了一辆推土机。

yingyinNormal.en: Yep. Thank Wolowitz. He set it up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢沃罗威茨吧。是他安排的。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll set up a meeting. Just you, me and him.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我会安排次会面，只有你我他三人。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. I'm gonna need a new set of these forms.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我需要新表格。

yingyinNormal.en: Maybe we don't need the set-navi. Let's go this way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 也许，我们不需要导航。我们走这边吧。

yingyinNormal.en: So you want to set the record straight. Indeed, Dave.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以你想建立一个记录。是的，戴夫。

yingyinNormal.en: Your reaction decision time will be set at 35 seconds.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的反应时间会被设定成35秒。

yingyinNormal.en: You must set aside your petty grievances with the dwarves.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们对矮人的小牢骚可以放在一边了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies》

yingyinNormal.en: Think back, Leonard. The littlest things can set women off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好好想想，莱纳德，再小的事情都能让女人爆发。

yingyinNormal.en: Just set it down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 放下就好。

yingyinNormal.en: That could be easily arranged. Ready, set, go? Do it. All right then. Ready. Set. Go.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那真是小菜一碟，各就各位，准备，开始？来吧。那好吧，预备，开始。

yingyinNormal.en: All right, I won't set one aside for you. But I must have it. Okay, I'll set one aside for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那我不给你留了。但我必须要拥有它行。那我给你留着。

yingyinNormal.en: A date? She's got a date? With who? I set her up with this actor on my show. You set her up? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她有约会？对方是谁？我撮合她跟一个男演员。你撮合她？不。

yingyinNormal.en: OK. We're all set. What do you mean we're all set? Well, I know that guy. He's gonna take care of it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，我都安排好了。什么意思？安排好什么了？我认识那个人，他会处理好的。

yingyinNormal.en: I will never get sick of you. I am set for life!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我永远都不会烦你。那我此生无忧了！

yingyinNormal.en: I was the one freaking set of footprints in the sand!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是那被人过了河就拆的桥！

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: It's not difficult to <highlight>set</highlight> targets for staff.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 给员工设定目标并不难。

examination_example.sentence: If we <highlight>set</highlight> an end-of-quarter deadline, we will never make it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果我们设定一个季度末的最后期限，我们将永远无法完成。

examination_example.sentence: Terms like unplug, offline, life-hack, bandwidth, and capacity are all about <highlight>setting</highlight> boundaries between the office and the home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 诸如拔掉插头、离线、生活黑客、带宽和能力等术语全都与设定工作与家庭之间的界线有关。

sense_info_list.en: a group of similar things that belong together in some way

examination_example.sentence: Another <highlight>set</highlight> of participants had to count backward from 1,000 by nines as they watched the clips.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 另一组参与者在观看视频时必须从1000开始倒数9。

examination_example.sentence: The growth of higher education manifests itself in at least three quite different ways, and these in turn have given rise to different <highlight>sets</highlight> of problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 高等教育的发展至少以三种截然不同的方式表现出来，而这三种方式又产生了不同的问题。

examination_example.sentence: A flashing <highlight>set</highlight> of healthy and clean, regular "pearly whites" was a rare sight in Victorian society.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在维多利亚时代的社会中，一套健康干净、整齐的“珍珠白”是很少见的。

examination_example.sentence: New standards are being <highlight>set</highlight> in Denmark.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 丹麦正在树立新的标准。

examination_example.sentence: The United States is trying to <highlight>set</highlight> voluntary standards for models and fashion images.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国正试图为模特和时尚形象树立自愿标准。

examination_example.sentence: He <highlight>set</highlight> an example for other journals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他为其他期刊树立了榜样。

examination_example.sentence: The most drastic, an thoroughly illegal, reaction has been the emergence of Sci-Hub, <highlight>set</highlight> up in 2012.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最激烈的、完全非法的反应是科幻中心的出现，建立于2012年。

examination_example.sentence: Britain is <highlight>setting</highlight> up a data ethics center.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国正在建立一个数据伦理中心。

examination_example.sentence: The Nobels themselves were <highlight>set</highlight> up by a very rich individual who had decided what he wanted to do with his own money.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 诺贝尔获得者本身也是由非常富有的个人，他们可以决定如何分配自己的钱。

examination_example.sentence: Every Saturday morning, at 9 am, more than 50, 000 runners <highlight>set</highlight> off to run 5km around their local park.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周六上午9点，超过50，000名跑步者出发，绕着他们当地的公园跑5公里。

examination_example.sentence: Most archaeological sites, however, are discovered by archaeologists who have <highlight>set</highlight> out to look for them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，大多数考古遗址都是由开始出发寻找它们的考古学家发现的。

examination_example.sentence: In South Carolina, a state-sponsored antismoking program called Rage Against the Haze <highlight>sets</highlight> out to make cigarettes uncool.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在南卡罗来纳州，一个由州政府赞助的名为“愤怒对抗阴霾”的禁烟项目开始让人们觉得吸烟一点儿也不酷。

examination_example.sentence: If the bills become law, state boards and commissions will be required to <highlight>set</highlight> aside 50 percent of board seats for women.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果这些法案成为法律，各州董事会和委员会将被要求为女性留出50%的董事会席位。

examination_example.sentence: The fund will also be used to compensate landowners who <highlight>set</highlight> aside habitat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该基金还将用于补偿留出栖息地的土地所有者。

examination_example.sentence: Scheduling regular times for reading helps encourage the efficiency mind-<highlight>set</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 安排规律的阅读时间有助于提高思维效率。

examination_example.sentence: No mind-<highlight>set</highlight> could be worse for losing yourself in a book.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有比让你自己迷失在一本书里更糟糕的思维模式了。

examination_example.sentence: You'd think this might fuel the efficiency mind-<highlight>set</highlight>, but such ritualistic behaviour helps us "step outside time's flow" into "soul time."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你可能会认为这可能会助长效率思维定势，但这种仪式行为有助于我们“走出时间之流”进入“灵魂时间”。

sense_info_list.en: put or bring into a specified state

examination_example.sentence: The living rats were 52 percent more likely on average to <highlight>set</highlight> the social robot free than the asocial one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 生物鼠解救社交机器鼠的几率比解救非社交机器鼠的几率平均高出52%。

examination_example.sentence: It <highlight>set</highlight> the trapped rats free.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它释放了被困的老鼠。

examination_example.sentence: Our legal system was designed to <highlight>set</highlight> law apart from politics precisely because they are so closely tied.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们的法律体系旨在将法律与政治区分开来，正是因为它们紧密相连。

sense_info_list.en: get something ready so that it comes into operation or can be used

examination_example.sentence: He suggested that preretirees should speak with a financial adviser to <highlight>set</highlight> long-term financial goals.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他建议退休前的人应该和财务顾问谈谈，制定长期的财务目标。

examination_example.sentence: Bob Liodice holds that <highlight>setting</highlight> DNT as a default goes against human nature.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Bob Liodice认为，将DNT设定为违约违背了人性。

examination_example.sentence: A series of fires (including those <highlight>set</highlight> by the British in 1814) and overcrowded conditions led to the construction of the existing Treasury Building.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一系列火灾（包括1814年英国人放的火）和过度拥挤的环境，才有了现在财政大楼的修建。

examination_example.sentence: Yet its report may well <highlight>set</highlight> back reform by obscuring the depth and breadth of the challenge.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，它的报告可能会掩盖挑战的深度和广度，从而阻碍改革。

examination_example.sentence: On May 31st Microsoft <highlight>set</highlight> off the row.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 5月31日，微软引发了这场争论。

sense_info_list.en: ready, prepared, or likely to do sth.
sense_info_list.zh: 做好准备的; 可能的

examination_example.sentence: Millennials were told that if you did well in school, got a decent degree, you would be <highlight>set</highlight> up for life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 千禧一代被告知，如果你在学校表现出色，拿到一个体面的学位，你就为生活做好准备了。

examination_example.sentence: Parents and teachers tend to be still <highlight>set</highlight> in the degree mindset.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 家长和老师仍然倾向于固守学位的观念。

examination_example.sentence: Marconi needed to achieve the goal that was <highlight>set</highlight> in his mind as an adolescent.

examination_example.sentence: As countries continue <highlight>setting</highlight> goals of reducing emissions, greater steps need to be taken to have a noticeable effect on the surrounding environment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着各国继续设定减排目标，需要采取更多的措施才能对周围环境产生显著影响。

examination_example.sentence: Entry level interviewees would do well to demonstrate a broad <highlight>set</highlight> of skills in most interviews.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 入门级面试者在大多数面试中都能很好地展示一系列的技能。

examination_example.sentence: It's important to have a wide skill <highlight>set</highlight> as many startups and small companies are moving really fast.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拥有广泛的技能非常重要，因为许多初创公司和小公司的发展速度非常快。

examination_example.sentence: It wasn't their skill <highlight>set</highlight> or other merits that got them the job.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 并不是他们的技能或其他优点让他们得到了这份工作。

sense_info_list.en: cause someone or something to start doing something

examination_example.sentence: China seems <highlight>set</highlight> to transition to become the key supplier of relevant science and technology to poorer countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国看上去可能要过渡成为向较贫穷国家提供相关科学技术的关键供应商。

examination_example.sentence: Scottish councils are <highlight>set</highlight> to be the first with the power to levy charges on visitors, with Edinburgh likely to lead the way.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 苏格兰议会将成为第一个有权向游客收费的地方，爱丁堡很可能会率先实施。

examination_example.sentence: The UK is <highlight>set</highlight> to adjust its policy on taxation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国将调整其税收政策。

examination_example.sentence: Finally, relevant regulatory authorities should also strictly monitor the behavior of pop stars and ensure that they <highlight>set</highlight> good examples for teenagers.

examination_example.sentence: The data <highlight>set</highlight> they used did not include economic data, so instead the researchers looked at whether the 2013-16 wellbeing decline was tracking economic indicators.

examination_example.sentence: "An ultimate face recognition algorithm should perform with billions of people in a data <highlight>set</highlight>, " the researchers wrote.

examination_example.sentence: MegaFace's creators say it's the largest publicly available facial-recognition data <highlight>set</highlight> out there.

examination_example.sentence: Training <highlight>sets</highlight> like the ones Google and Facebook have are private.

examination_example.sentence: The concept of behavioral activation, whereby engaging in a behavior can <highlight>set</highlight> you on the path to then achieving your goals.

examination_example.sentence: There was a hill where gas leakage was so noticeable that schoolboys would sometimes <highlight>set</highlight> the hill on fire.

examination_example.sentence: He borrowed technical details from many sources, but what <highlight>set</highlight> him apart was a self-confident vision of the power of communication technology.

word_usage.usage: set作形容词时，无比较级和最高级形式。

set a good better example to sb. 是习惯用法，意为“给某人树立榜样”，其中介词 to不能用for替代。
也可用 set sb. a good example表达相同的意思。
表达“动身/出发去某地”，往往用set off/out for...表示，其中介词 for不能用to替代。
表达“放火，纵火”，用set fire表示，fire前面不加冠词。
set sb. free为习惯用法，表示“释放某人”，这里宾语sb.必须放在set和 free之间，不能置后。

examination_example.sentence: One day, the teacher <highlight>set</highlight> an exam and a boy called Robert signed his exam using Anna's name.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有一天，老师安排了一场考试，一个叫罗伯特的男孩用了安娜的名字在试卷上签名。

sense_info_list.zh: (set to)起劲地干起来; 毅然开始做

examination_example.sentence: So Claire organized a group of kids and grown-ups who <highlight>set</highlight> to work raising the rest.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以克莱尔组织了一群孩子和努力工作抚养这些孩子的成年人。

word_usage.usage: set作形容词时，无比较级和最高级形式。

set a good better example to sb. 是习惯用法，意为“给某人树立榜样”，其中介词 to不能用for替代。
也可用 set sb. a good example表达相同的意思。
表达“动身/出发去某地”，往往用set off/out for...表示，其中介词 for不能用to替代。
表达“放火，纵火”，用set fire表示，fire前面不加冠词。
set sb. free为习惯用法，表示“释放某人”，这里宾语sb.必须放在set和 free之间，不能置后。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 指小心地把人或物平放或横放，侧重动作安稳。
较正式用词，指把某物放在一个正确的位置上，侧重动作的正确。
普通用词，含义较广泛。指把人或物置于某处，并将其留在该处。
普通用词，指为了某种目的而将人或物放在一定位置上。指物时多指立着放。
